George Simeon S. - Vocals | The Investigators
















































 








The Investigators






 



Home
Band
Video
Medien
Kontakt
 










					Band					










George Simeon S. Vocals


















 
George Simeon S. was born a while ago into a bitterly poor family in the village of Styllos, northwest of Famagusta, northern Cyprus – when northern Cyprus was not yet turkish.

George and his 17 sisters and brothers never went to school, since there was no money in the house. Although he could neither read nor write - and still can’t - he managed to open a porn shop at the age of 12. Unfortunately, he was ahead of his time and there was not yet a demand for porn products in Styllos. So he became a priest, serving the church of the Holy Kolokasi.

There, he started to sing the Holy Songs of Cyprus Vegetables on a regular basis and was heard doing so by a strange man from abroad, named Malcom the Eejit. It was his idea to combine George’s early porno-shop-plan with an new kind of music: The Sex Pissers were born.

Since George Simeon S.‘s voice was too good and too unusual for the simple Sex-Pissers-Songs and since George didn’t want to give up singing about Kologasi, he joined the famous Punk Rock Band THE INVESTIGATORS, an outstanding group of Vegetables.

That’s the simple story about one of the most impressive singers the village of Styllos ever produced.

Keep on punk rocking!






Band MembersGeorge Simeon S – Vocals
Fjodor F. Fjodor – Bass
Vincent D. Wit – Guitar
Reiner Gamma – Drums
 




 


















